!! What it does

Theme provides a centralised set of CSS classes (prefix `rr-`) used across all rimir plugins. It eliminates duplicate styling by offering consistent patterns for tabs, panels, tables, callouts, notices, badges, forms, and the settings hub layout.

!! Features

* ''Tabs'' — `rr-tabs`, `rr-tab`, `rr-tab-active` for horizontal tab bars
* ''Panels'' — bordered containers with padded content area
* ''Tables'' — full-width collapsed tables with error/warning row styles
* ''Callouts'' — four types (info, warning, tip, danger) via reusable template
* ''Notices'' — alert banners (warning, info, danger, success)
* ''Badges'' — circular and rectangular pill badges
* ''Forms'' — styled inputs and flex row layout
* ''Settings hub'' — sidebar + content layout for the core-hook settings panel
* ''Utilities'' — muted, mono, nowrap, small helper classes

!! Plugin files

|!File |!Role |
|`styles.tid` |All CSS definitions (`rr-*` prefix) |
|`callout.tid` |Reusable callout box template |
|`notice.tid` |Reusable notice banner template |

